Package net.sf.jguiraffe.gui.builder.components

Class ComponentManagerImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jguiraffe.gui.builder.components.ComponentManagerImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ComponentManager
    public class ComponentManagerImpl
extends Object
implements ComponentManager
    This is a test implementation of the ComponentManager interface. Instead of real components only strings are created whose names represent the corresponding components. So the builder's results should be easy to test.
    Version:
    $Id: ComponentManagerImpl.java 205 2012-01-29 18:29:57Z oheger $
    Author:
    Oliver Heger

        protected ComponentHandler createHandler​(String compName,

                                         InputComponentTag tag,
                                         Class defType)
                                  throws FormBuilderException
        Creates a dummy component handler object.
        Parameters:

        Throws:

      • createHandler

        protected <T extends ComponentHandler> T createHandler​(Class<T> ifcClass,
                                                       String compName,
                                                       StringBuilder buf,
                                                       Class<?> defType)
                                                throws FormBuilderException
        Creates a dummy component handler of the given interface class. This method can be used if the handler needs to implement an extended interface. It creates a proxy that implements this interface. The proxy supports the methods of the basic ComponentHandler interface, but has empty dummy implementations for extended methods.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the handler interface
        Parameters:
        ifcClass - the class of the handler interface to implement
        compName - the name of the component
        buf - the target buffer
        defType - the default component type
        Returns:
        the component handler
        Throws:
        FormBuilderException - if an error occurs
